Articles.Content:
Okay since my computer still works and I redownloaded KSP anyways (computer purge) I slapped this together to celebrate.

Download [https://www.dropbox.com/s/xt19oy8x3yyqd6n/Kepler.craft?dl=0](https://www.dropbox.com/s/xt19oy8x3yyqd6n/Kepler.craft?dl=0)

[![screenshot48_zpspuendlry.png](http://i1383.photobucket.com/albums/ah315/Yukon0009/screenshot48_zpspuendlry.png)](http://s1383.photobucket.com/user/Yukon0009/media/screenshot48_zpspuendlry.png.html)[![screenshot58_zpshim8f97u.png](http://i1383.photobucket.com/albums/ah315/Yukon0009/screenshot58_zpshim8f97u.png)](http://s1383.photobucket.com/user/Yukon0009/media/screenshot58_zpshim8f97u.png.html)

Looking nice! Delta II is one of my favorite modern rockets, in part due to the fact that it launched the Mars Exploration Rovers, which are single-handedly responsible for making me the space nerd I am today.![:D](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif) Kepler itself is pretty good too, interesting use of the Round-8 tanks.

Did this craft's creation have anything to do with the fact that Kepler just discovered one of the most earth-like exoplanets a few days ago?
Yep, I was on the internet and found out about it.
